Entrypoints:
============
By default the container will run the "dollar-tracker" script created by the setup.py config file with the "track" parameter.
to overwrite this parameter, we just need to pass the parameter after the image name in the docker run command 

volume history:
===============
volume set to /usr/src/app/dollar-tracker which is the working directory of the container
when running the application we need to set -v <host_folder>:/usr/src/app/dollar-tracker  so the application can be run without especify the --path option

dollar points:
=============
cron job that runs periodically 
	-v <host_folder>:/usr/src/app/dollar-tracker dollar-tracker track: will add points to the history that will be saved in /usr/src/app/dollar-tracker


docker run -v /home/mauro/Inversiones/:/usr/src/app/dollar-tracker -i -t dollar-tracker

viewing the plot:
================
run the container with
	-v <host_folder>:/usr/src/app/dollar-tracker dollar-tracker plot this will create a HTML file in the host 

docker run -v /home/mauro/Inversiones/:/usr/src/app/dollar-tracker -i -t dollar-tracker plot	  




